	<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#666699" vAlign="TOP">
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">I don't have a problem in theory with folks buying plat. There are people who value their time more than their money, and for them, buying plat instead of farming it is a good value to them. Or, as I said to my sister yesterday, who spent $400 on a fancy new kitchen sink, that's no different than me spending $400 on a fancy new game card. She's a baker, I'm a gamer. <br />
<br />
However, outside of theory, it IS against the EULA. When you click that button that says "I agree", you are agreeing to abide by the terms of the agreement to play the game. It's their servers, their rules. If you get your plat deleted or your account banned, don't come crying.<br />
<br />
Or, to quote Army of Darkness:<br />
<br />
"Good ... bad ... I'm the guy with the gun."<br />
<br />
...Mille</font></p>
	
