	<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#666699" vAlign="TOP">
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">Okay... I've given you my thoughts with my moderator hat on.  Let me take that hat off and give you my thoughts as a private individual.<br />
<br />
I'll start by saying that the purchase or sale of platinum does not hurt me personally.  Without ever purchasing or selling pp, I've reached that stage of the game where there is no item or spell in the game available in the bazaar which would be an upgrade to my character and there has been no such item for months.  The only reason why I'm not sitting on an enormous pool of pp is my tradeskill habit and the fact that I've stopped worrying about reagent costs.<br />
<br />
Therefore, I have no personal axe to grind.<br />
<br />
I'm a former officer of a raiding guild, who's moved to a guild at a much lower level of achievement because my new guild is focused on roleplaying rather than raiding and that's what I enjoy.  I know people who have purchased EQ items for RL money.  I know someone who purchased a Sleeper's Tomb key for several hundred dollars, and someone else who purchased an Ornate Breastplate mold although I'm unaware of the price.  For rather smaller amounts of money, I've seen many others purchase things like FT3 boots, Staff of Flowing Water, and whatever.<br />
<br />
I've also seen the kind of person who will farm a Sleeper's Tomb key or an Ornate Breastplate mold.  They tend to be prepared to act very discourteously towards other people, sometimes even training or KSing in order to ensure that they get this week's EQ items sale paycheck.<br />
<br />
I'll repeat that this doesn't hurt me.  The content that I'm interested in is instanced so there's no possibility of training or KSing anyway.<br />
<br />
But I do know it goes on, and I find it distasteful.  I'd like to see it coming to an end.</font></p>
	
	<p>What on earth is [url=http://yexx.proboards39.com]Yexx[/url] ?</p>
	<p></p>
	</td></tr></table>
